A duplicate of #1654 with additional commits that automatically address incorrect style, created by [Restyled][]. Since the original Pull Request was opened as a fork in a contributor's repository, we are unable to create a Pull Request branching from it with only the style fixes. The following Restylers [made fixes](https://restyled.io/gh/TokTok/repos/c-toxcore/jobs/1410260): - astyle - clang-format To incorporate these changes, you can either: 1. Merge this Pull Request *instead of* the original, or 1. Ask your contributor to locally incorporate these commits and push them to the original Pull Request
Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. To disable it, see our [documentation][]. commit.message:
No longer send chat ID hash in plaintext packet headers

This was used to identify the group that a groupchat packet was intended for
however due to the public nature of DHT groupchats, it would expose the fact
that someone was in a particular group to anyone who looked.

We now use a hash of the recipient's group permanent public key for handshake
packets, and a hash of the recipient's session public key associated
with the sender's connection for all other packets.

This significantly reduces the ability of adversaries from determining that a
target is in a particular group.

be able to have multiple keys in multiple groups that create the same
hash.

Make some improvements to error handling inbound packets

 A packet handler should return success if we want to
send the sender an ack even if the packet contained
invalid data. This is to prevent cases where an out

in the send queue and blocks subsequent packets.

to know about the failure.

commit.message:
Use pointers to shared state in Moderation object

Instead of having to maintain and sync copies of shared state
or passing variables to functions, we just use pointers now.
This guarantees that the shared state will never accidentally
go out of sync and makes things a lot simpler
